  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Thursday. School announced last night that a typhoon was coming, which means today is officially a no-school, stay-inside kind of day.",
      "zh": "星期四。學校昨晚就宣布颱風要來了，代表今天正式是個不用上學、待在家裡的日子。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The morning started strangely calm, with thick fog covering the street outside, the kind of quiet that feels like it is hiding something.",
      "zh": "早上一開始出奇地平靜，濃霧籠罩著外面的街道，那種安靜感覺像是在隱藏什麼事。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By noon, the sky turned completely cloudy, and by early afternoon, we heard our first real crash of thunder.",
      "zh": "到了中午，天空整個變得烏雲密布，下午稍早我們就聽到了第一聲真正的雷聲。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William counted the seconds between the thunder and the following flash of light, convinced this made him some kind of storm scientist.",
      "zh": "William 開始數雷聲和後面那道閃光之間的秒數，深信這讓他變成某種暴風科學家。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Dad went around the house checking windows for safety, taping a few weak spots so nothing dangerous would fly in during the storm.",
      "zh": "爸爸繞著屋子檢查每扇窗戶的安全，把幾個比較脆弱的地方貼上膠帶，免得暴風時有危險的東西飛進來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"A typhoon is not something to be careless about,\" he said. \"Respect the danger, and you will be fine.\"",
      "zh": "「颱風不是可以粗心大意的事，」他說：「尊重它的危險性，你就會平安無事。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "With no internet interruptions today, I finally sat down to finish my geography homework about Taiwan's varied landscape.",
      "zh": "今天沒有網路中斷的問題，我終於可以坐下來完成我的台灣多樣地形地理作業。"
    },
    {
      "en": "My textbook explained how Taiwan's location, sitting near the coast with tall mountains rising just behind it, makes the island's climate perfect for producing typhoons almost every year.",
      "zh": "課本解釋，台灣的地理位置緊鄰海岸，後方又緊接著高聳的山脈，這樣的地形讓這座島的氣候幾乎每年都很容易產生颱風。"
    },
    {
      "en": "It also mentioned a quiet green valley on the other side of those mountains, protected just enough from the worst of the wind.",
      "zh": "課本還提到那些山脈另一側有一座安靜的翠綠山谷，剛好受到足夠的保護，躲過最猛烈的風勢。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Further inland, thick forest covers much of the mountainside, holding the soil in place during heavy typhoon rain.",
      "zh": "再往內陸走，茂密的森林覆蓋了大部分山坡，在颱風豪雨期間幫忙固定住土壤。"
    },
    {
      "en": "My textbook compared this climate to a dry desert far away, where storms like today's almost never happen at all.",
      "zh": "課本把這種氣候拿來跟遙遠一個乾燥的沙漠比較，那裡幾乎從來不會發生像今天這樣的暴風。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I found an old photo on my phone from our beach trip last summer, sand between my toes, completely opposite of today's gray, stormy sky.",
      "zh": "我在手機裡找到去年夏天海邊之旅的舊照片，腳趾間全是沙子，跟今天灰濛濛的暴風天完全相反。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan sent the whole class a message, joking that surviving a typhoon safely at home is technically still \"attending school in spirit.\"",
      "zh": "潘老師傳訊息給全班，開玩笑說安全地在家躲颱風，某種精神層面上也算是「有到校上課」。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He also reminded us that Taiwan faces both typhoons and earthquakes, two very different kinds of danger that require two very different kinds of safety habits.",
      "zh": "他也提醒我們，台灣同時要面對颱風和地震這兩種完全不同的危險，需要兩種完全不同的安全習慣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"A typhoon gives you warning days in advance,\" he wrote. \"An earthquake gives you none at all. Prepare for both anyway.\"",
      "zh": "「颱風會提前好幾天給你警告，」他寫道：「地震完全不會給你任何警告，但兩種都要提前做好準備。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "By evening, the wind outside was loud enough to rattle the windows Dad had taped earlier, and Perry refused to go anywhere near the back door.",
      "zh": "到了晚上，外面的風大到把爸爸早上貼過膠帶的窗戶震得咯咯作響，Perry 完全不敢靠近後門一步。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia made extra soup, saying a stormy night always tastes better with something warm, no matter how loud the thunder gets outside.",
      "zh": "Sophia 多煮了一些湯，說暴風夜不管外面雷聲多大，喝點溫熱的東西總是比較對味。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Lesson of the day: a no-school typhoon day sounds fun until the thunder starts, and then it just feels like the whole sky is showing off.",
      "zh": "今日心得：不用上學的颱風天聽起來很好玩，直到雷聲開始響，感覺就像整片天空在炫耀自己有多厲害。"
    }
  ],
  "quiz": [
